The paper deals with the visualization and interpretation of deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of sensitivity-based approaches and deconvolution methods, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the practical implications of the results, which could be relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) and other areas of computer science.
